<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-27T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="1286" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1286">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90J/1–1745: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul at Aden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-27T21:00:00-04:00">January
                                    27, 1945—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6. Your proposed informal visit to the Yemen meets with Department’s
                            approval. Bearing in mind that this Government has not accorded official
                            recognition to the Yemen, you should listen to such proposals or
                            suggestions as Yemeni officials may make to you, stating that you will
                            be glad to convey them to your Government, but you should, of course,
                            make no commitments of any kind.</p>
                        <p>Please report fully to Department upon your visit.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>